47:08.675 --> 47:11.545
My name 
is Rocío Picado Herrero. 


47:11.545 --> 47:16.817
I studied chemistry 
at the University of Salamanca, in Spain. 


47:16.817 --> 47:20.087
I specialize in organic chemistry. 


47:20.087 --> 47:23.690
This field focuses 
on the study of the carbon atom 


47:23.690 --> 47:27.000
and all the compounds 
that are derived from this atom.


47:28.895 --> 47:32.365
I believed that life 
came about through evolution. 


47:32.365 --> 47:35.435
I remember seeing a picture 
in a natural science book 


47:35.435 --> 47:38.772
that depicted the embryos 
of different vertebrates, 


47:38.772 --> 47:43.610
and in the early stages of development, 
the similarities were outstanding. 


47:43.610 --> 47:46.780
But when I started studying 
at the university, 


47:46.780 --> 47:49.182
I began studying 
in detail the process 


47:49.182 --> 47:51.985
on which 
the evolution theory is based. 


47:51.985 --> 47:55.388
To my surprise, 
I discovered that these processes 


47:55.388 --> 47:57.723
were not proven facts. 


47:57.723 --> 47:59.793
As a chemist, I’m fascinated 


47:59.793 --> 48:02.930
by the distribution 
of atoms within a molecule.


48:02.930 --> 48:06.333
In living creatures, 
the 20 amino acids 


48:06.333 --> 48:09.068
that are vital 
for the synthesis of life, 


48:09.068 --> 48:12.138
the basic proteins 
required for life, 


48:12.138 --> 48:16.810
interestingly, 
are all levorotatory or left-handed.


48:16.810 --> 48:20.413
So when a ray 
of polarized light arrives, 


48:20.413 --> 48:24.416
these amino acids 
divert the light toward the left. 


48:24.417 --> 48:29.089
There is no explanation for this 
because the logical thing would be 


48:29.088 --> 48:33.026
that if this were a random process, 
half would be right-handed 


48:33.027 --> 48:36.000
and the other half 
would be left-handed.


48:40.600 --> 48:45.572
I asked myself, ‘How could evolution 
produce compounds that are levorotatory


48:45.572 --> 48:48.000
and precisely the ones 
essential for life?’


48:53.147 --> 48:56.884
In the end, I had to conclude 
that there must be a force, 


48:56.883 --> 49:00.320
a Designer, a Creator of life 
and of the elements 


49:00.320 --> 49:03.023
and the amino acids 
required for life.


49:03.023 --> 49:05.525
Even though 
I had a religious upbringing, 


49:05.525 --> 49:09.462
my ideas were not clear 
as to who God was. 


49:09.462 --> 49:12.532
I merely viewed him 
as a Supreme Being 


49:12.532 --> 49:15.000
before whom 
we would be held accountable.


49:16.803 --> 49:18.971
The Bible 
is not a science textbook. 


49:18.972 --> 49:22.142
Its purpose is not to describe 
the universe we live in 


49:22.142 --> 49:24.645
or the laws 
that regulate our universe. 


49:24.645 --> 49:27.413
But when it does mention science, 


49:27.413 --> 49:31.351
and when it discusses scientific matters, 
it does so with great accuracy. 


49:31.352 --> 49:35.355
And undoubtedly the greatest benefit 
is that it allows me to enjoy 


49:35.355 --> 49:38.592
a personal relationship 
with the Creator of the universe


49:38.592 --> 49:42.000
—a universe that fascinates me 
from a scientific perspective.


49:46.533 --> 49:48.535
My name is Davey Loos. 


49:48.535 --> 49:51.905
I studied biochemistry 
at the University of Leuven in Belgium, 


49:51.905 --> 49:55.608
and after that time 
I did a PhD in the same area.


49:55.608 --> 49:59.445
When I was a young child, 
I believed in the Bible. 


49:59.445 --> 50:03.717
But growing up, 
I kind of lost my interest in it. 


50:03.717 --> 50:06.620
When you go to university 
and you study life sciences 


50:06.620 --> 50:08.922
or biochemistry, for example,


50:08.922 --> 50:12.625
you get introduced into the idea 
of the origin of life very quickly 


50:12.625 --> 50:14.627
and also into the principle 
of evolution.


50:14.627 --> 50:17.297
The professors 
who taught these courses, 


50:17.297 --> 50:19.767
they were really scientists 
with long careers, 


50:19.767 --> 50:23.970
and they were well-established scientists, 
and we had a lot of respect for them. 


50:23.970 --> 50:28.000
So there was just no way to really question
the principle of evolution.


50:29.743 --> 50:33.746
In 1999, there was a war 
in Europe—in Kosovo—


50:33.747 --> 50:36.950
and I remember reading 
in the Bible as a child 


50:36.950 --> 50:41.755
about the future events 
that would take place, 


50:41.755 --> 50:45.525
and I started wondering whether the war 
in Kosovo was one of those events. 


50:45.525 --> 50:48.000
So that lead me 
to pick up the Bible again.


50:49.462 --> 50:53.700
At the time, I felt that I had to reexamine 
my beliefs about the origin of life 


50:53.700 --> 50:57.000
and also about the principle 
of evolution.


50:58.705 --> 51:01.708
Based on the theory of evolution, 
we would expect to see 


51:01.708 --> 51:05.878
an abundance of transitional forms 
to be present in the fossil record. 


51:05.878 --> 51:09.181
But when we do look at the fossil evidence,
we just don’t see that. 


51:09.182 --> 51:11.685
We see that the major species 


51:11.685 --> 51:14.187
come into existence 
at specific times, 


51:14.187 --> 51:16.957
and their form and structure 
is still exactly the same


51:16.957 --> 51:19.125
as their form 
and structure today.


51:19.125 --> 51:23.630
It was actually Darwin himself 
who wrote in his book 


51:23.630 --> 51:27.700
that the biggest objection 
that could be brought against this theory 


51:27.700 --> 51:30.870
would be the fact 
that the fossil record 


51:30.870 --> 51:34.808
does not show an abundance 
of transitional forms. 


51:34.808 --> 51:39.045
And that’s what really happens 
if you look at the set of data


51:39.045 --> 51:43.817
—the fossil record seems to prove 
the opposite of evolution.


51:43.817 --> 51:48.222
As a biochemist, 
I had the opportunity to learn about 


51:48.222 --> 51:50.890
and study 
many different biomolecules. 


51:50.890 --> 51:54.393
And I observed 
that pretty much every biomolecule 


51:54.393 --> 51:56.563
is really a complex molecule. 


51:56.563 --> 52:00.900
We can look at them 
as nanoscale molecular motors 


52:00.900 --> 52:05.000
or machines that are performing 
very complex and specific tasks.


52:06.372 --> 52:11.210
For me, the complexity that we see in nature
and the complexity in those molecules 


52:11.210 --> 52:15.282
points to the fact 
that there really is a Creator.


52:15.282 --> 52:17.950
Did you see common ground 
that could help you 


52:17.950 --> 52:21.722
in your next discussion 
with someone who believes in evolution? 


52:21.722 --> 52:24.790
When Sister Picado Herrero’s 
chemistry research 


52:24.790 --> 52:26.793
showed evidence of design,


52:26.793 --> 52:31.063
she called to mind her view of God 
from her religious upbringing. 


52:31.063 --> 52:33.666
The person you meet 
who believes in evolution 


52:33.667 --> 52:37.337
might also have unanswered questions 
about God from their upbringing, 


52:37.337 --> 52:40.207
and they may respond 
to the simple evidences


52:40.207 --> 52:42.642
of a Creator 
that you present. 


52:42.642 --> 52:45.579
Brother Loos 
was moved by world events 


52:45.578 --> 52:48.981
to pick up the Bible 
and reexamine his beliefs.


52:48.982 --> 52:52.652
Everyone we meet, 
even firm believers in evolution, 


52:52.652 --> 52:57.657
are affected by world conditions 
and may listen to our message of hope. 


52:57.657 --> 53:00.794
So when someone says 
that he believes in evolution, 


53:00.793 --> 53:03.996
don’t be quick to assume 
that he’ll reject the good news. 


53:03.997 --> 53:08.735
Really, our ministry 
and other aspects of life often improve 


53:08.735 --> 53:11.538
